The paper discusses issues related to implementing algorithms and models in computer science and computational disciplines, as well as the need for fair benchmarking and publicly available benchmark sets. These topics are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE), computer engineering (cs.CE), programming languages (cs.PL), distributed computing (cs.DC), and databases (cs.DB).
